    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">K-Electric Offline Payment Methods — Cash, Bank, Shop 2026</h1>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-lg mb-4">While online payment through JazzCash, EasyPaisa, and banking apps is the most convenient way to pay your <strong>K-Electric bill</strong>, many consumers in Karachi still prefer or need offline payment methods. This includes senior citizens who don't use smartphones, low-income households without bank accounts, and consumers who simply prefer paying in cash. K-Electric has the most extensive offline payment network of any Pakistani utility — with over 4,000 payment touchpoints across Karachi alone. This guide covers every offline payment option, expected processing times, and tips to avoid common issues.</p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800">Quick Summary: Pay your K-Electric bill in cash at any HBL, UBL, MCB, NBP, or Bank Alfalah branch in Karachi; at any shop displaying the 1Bill/Infinia logo; at K-Electric customer service centers (I.I. Chundrigar Road HQ, Clifton, Gulshan, North Nazimabad); or at NADRA e-Sahulat centers. Bring your 13-digit K-Electric account number.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">All Offline Payment Methods for K-Electric Bills</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">K-Electric offers multiple offline payment channels. Pick the one most convenient for you:</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Method</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Where</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Fee</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Reflect Time</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-neutral-200">
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Bank branch</td><td class="p-3">HBL, UBL, MCB, NBP, Bank Alfalah in Karachi</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">4 hours</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">K-Electric CSC</td><td class="p-3">KE Customer Service Centers (Clifton, Gulshan, Nazimabad, etc.)</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">1Bill shop</td><td class="p-3">Any shop with 1Bill/Infinia logo</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 30–50</td><td class="p-3">12–24 hours</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">NADRA e-Sahulat</td><td class="p-3">Any NADRA center</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 30</td><td class="p-3">24–48 hours</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">ATM</td><td class="p-3">Any bank ATM (HBL, UBL, MCB, Bank Alfalah)</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Post office</td><td class="p-3">GPO Karachi, Saddar GPO</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 20</td><td class="p-3">2–3 days</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">K-Electric mobile van</td><td class="p-3">Rotating locations in Karachi (check ke.com.pk)</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Step-by-Step: Paying K-Electric Bill at a Bank Branch</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Paying at a bank branch is the most common offline method. Here's the exact process:</p>
    <ol class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li><strong>Bring your K-Electric bill.</strong> If you lost the printed bill, download a duplicate from <a href="/k-electric-bill/" class="text-primary-600 underline">pakistanbill.online/k-electric-bill/</a> and print it.</li>
      <li><strong>Visit any HBL, UBL, MCB, NBP, or Bank Alfalah branch in Karachi.</strong> Branches outside Karachi may not accept K-Electric bills — call ahead to confirm.</li>
      <li><strong>Go to the Utility Bills counter.</strong> Take a token if the bank uses a token system.</li>
      <li><strong>Present your bill to the teller.</strong> The teller will scan the barcode or manually enter your 13-digit account number.</li>
      <li><strong>Pay the amount in cash.</strong> Try to bring exact change — tellers often don't have small change.</li>
      <li><strong>Get the stamped receipt.</strong> The teller returns the bill with a "PAID" stamp, plus a separate payment receipt.</li>
      <li><strong>Keep the receipt for 3 months</strong> — in case of dispute, this is your proof of payment.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Step-by-Step: Paying K-Electric Bill at a Shop</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">If you don't have a bank account or want to pay outside banking hours, shops with 1Bill/Infinia logos are convenient:</p>
    <ol class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li><strong>Find a shop with the 1Bill or Infinia logo</strong> — usually displayed on the door or counter. Most utility bill shops, general stores in markets, and pan shops in Karachi accept K-Electric bills.</li>
      <li><strong>Bring your K-Electric account number</strong> — 13 digits. You can find it on your bill or in your payment history if you've paid before.</li>
      <li><strong>Tell the shopkeeper the bill type</strong> — "K-Electric bill" — and provide the account number.</li>
      <li><strong>Pay cash plus the shop fee</strong> — usually Rs. 30–50 per transaction.</li>
      <li><strong>Get the printed receipt</strong> — the shopkeeper prints a small receipt with payment confirmation, transaction ID, and date.</li>
      <li><strong>Save the receipt</strong> until the payment reflects on your next K-Electric bill (typically 24 hours).</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">K-Electric Customer Service Centers (CSCs)</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">K-Electric operates its own payment counters at customer service centers across Karachi. These are the most reliable for instant payment reflection:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>K-Electric HQ — I.I. Chundrigar Road</strong> (main center, near Tower)</li>
      <li><strong>Clifton CSC</strong> — Boat Basin, Clifton Block 5</li>
      <li><strong>Gulshan-e-Iqbal CSC</strong> — Main Rashid Minhas Road, near Hasan Square</li>
      <li><strong>North Nazimabad CSC</strong> — Block H, near Hyderi Market</li>
      <li><strong>Korangi CSC</strong> — Sector 32-A, near Korangi Crossing</li>
      <li><strong>Malir CSC</strong> — Main Shah Faisal Road, near Malir Halt</li>
      <li><strong>Bahadurabad CSC</strong> — Bahadurabad Chowrangi</li>
      <li><strong>Federal B Area CSC</strong> — Block 13, near Dastagir</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">CSCs are open 9 AM – 5 PM, Monday to Saturday (closed Sundays and public holidays). Payments made at CSCs reflect instantly in K-Electric's system — no waiting period.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Common Issues & How to Resolve Them</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">Issue: Paid but bill showing unpaid</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">This happens if the bank/shop delayed posting the payment. Wait 24 hours, then check your bill online. If still showing unpaid, call K-Electric helpline 118 with your payment receipt number. Most disputes are resolved within 48 hours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">Issue: Wrong account number entered at shop</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">If the shopkeeper entered a wrong digit, the payment went to someone else's account. Immediately call K-Electric helpline 118 with your receipt — they can reverse the transaction within 24 hours if reported promptly. After 24 hours, recovery is much harder.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">Issue: Bank refused to accept the bill</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Some bank branches refuse K-Electric bills from outside their immediate service area. If refused, try a different bank or use a 1Bill shop instead. You can also file a complaint with K-Electric — they have agreements with all major banks for bill acceptance.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">Issue: Due date is tomorrow and payment not reflecting</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Visit a K-Electric CSC instead of a bank — CSC payments reflect instantly. If you can't reach a CSC, call K-Electric 118 and inform them you've already paid — they can place a temporary hold on disconnection while the payment clears.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Tips for Smooth K-Electric Offline Payment</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Pay 3–5 days before due date</strong> — gives buffer for slow-processing channels like post office or 1Bill shops.</li>
      <li><strong>Always keep the receipt</strong> for at least 3 months. Without it, you cannot prove payment if disputes arise.</li>
      <li><strong>Take a photo of the stamped bill</strong> immediately after payment — serves as backup if you lose the receipt.</li>
      <li><strong>Visit CSCs for last-day payments</strong> — instant reflection, no risk of late surcharge.</li>
      <li><strong>Avoid agents outside bank branches</strong> who offer to pay on your behalf for a fee — they often run off with the cash.</li>
      <li><strong>For large bills (Rs. 50,000+)</strong>, pay at a K-Electric CSC rather than a shop — better security and instant reflection.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Where can I pay K-Electric bill in cash?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Pay K-Electric bill in cash at any HBL, UBL, MCB, NBP, or Bank Alfalah branch in Karachi. Also payable at K-Electric customer service centers (I.I. Chundrigar Road HQ, Clifton, Gulshan, North Nazimabad) and NADRA e-Sahulat centers.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Can I pay K-Electric bill at shop?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Yes. Any shop displaying the 1Bill or Infinia logo accepts K-Electric bill payments. Provide your 13-digit K-Electric account number and pay cash. The shopkeeper gives you a receipt with payment confirmation.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is the K-Electric helpline for payment issues?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Call K-Electric helpline 118 (from Karachi) or 021-99000000 from mobile. For payment disputes (paid but bill showing unpaid), call 021-99008200 with your payment receipt.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How long does K-Electric cash payment take to reflect?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Cash payments at bank branches and K-Electric centers reflect within 4 working hours. Shop payments via 1Bill take 12-24 hours to reflect. NADRA e-Sahulat payments take 24-48 hours.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Can I pay K-Electric bill with credit card?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Yes. K-Electric accepts credit/debit card payments through its official website ke.com.pk or mobile app. Some bank branches also accept card payments at the counter. Card payments reflect instantly.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Is there a fee for paying K-Electric bill in cash?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Paying at bank branches and K-Electric CSCs is free. Shops charge Rs. 30-50 per transaction. NADRA e-Sahulat charges Rs. 30. Post office charges Rs. 20. ATMs and credit card payments are free.</div></details>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-primary-900 mb-2">Check Your K-Electric Bill First</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-700 mb-4 text-sm">View your bill amount and due date before paying.</p>
